Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm cubes (no need to peel). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds, chop into 2cm pieces. Pop the potato and pepper on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{some} and sprinkle over the @Cajun spice mix{1}. Toss and roast on the top shelf of your oven, ~{20-25%minutes}, turn halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Use less spice if you don't like heat.

Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat and add the @chorizo{60%g} and the onion and cook, stirring regularly, until the onion has softened and the chorizo is crispy, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic to the onion and cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Pour the @water{300%ml} into the #saucepan{} with the onion and garlic and bring to the boil. When boiling, add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes}.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved). Put the @soured cream{150%g} in a #bowl{} and stir in the lime zest. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir together. Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone, turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh onto a #board{}. Chop into 2cm chunks. Put the avocado into a bowl and squeeze over half the lime juice.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1} in a #colander{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Preheat your #grill{} to high. Once the rice is cooked, stir through the kidney beans, remaining lime juice and half the coriander, then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{}.

Add the roasted vegetables to the dish with the rice and gently combine everything together. Sprinkle over the grated cheese and pop the dish under your grill until the cheese is bubbling, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from your grill and scatter over the avocado. Dollop the soured cream across the top and sprinkle with the remaining coriander. Share between your bowls. Enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've added chorizo to your meal, add it to the pan when you add the onion and cook for the same amount of time. Follow the rest of the recipe as instructed.